  "drafts": {
    "full_draft": "A celebration of life at Sunset Cliffs on April 5 — a place that clearly meant something to him, and music that feels like it belongs to him rather than to the occasion. That distinction matters, and the fact that you're looking for presence rather than performance tells me you understand exactly what this moment needs.\n\nThe thing that goes wrong at gatherings like this is a musician who treats it like a gig: a setlist, a volume they picked in a parking lot, music that performs at people instead of moving through them. What I do is different. I listen to the space before I play. I calibrate to the wind, the voices, the pauses. The guitar sits underneath the moment, not on top of it.\n\nSunset Cliffs is exposed, and sea wind can swallow an unamplified instrument — so I bring a small, unobtrusive sound system that adds just enough carry without changing the feeling of the space. It'll still feel like a man playing guitar at the edge of the water.\n\nFor one hour of solo classical guitar, the rate is $595. April 5 is close, so if you'd like to confirm the date, I can hold it for you now.\n\nAlex Guillen\n(619) 755-3246",
